1
00:00:08,476 --> 00:00:09,476
A wyvern?

2
00:00:09,599 --> 00:00:10,599
A wyvern?

3
00:00:11,156 --> 00:00:14,182
It looks like a mage is controlling it.

4
00:00:14,660 --> 00:00:16,300
What do you think, Chancellor?

5
00:00:16,888 --> 00:00:19,873
Wyverns are fundamentally pack animals,

6
00:00:19,874 --> 00:00:23,112
so one would never attack
a village on its own.

7
00:00:23,826 --> 00:00:25,635
Plus, that mage is present.

8
00:00:26,140 --> 00:00:28,439
There could be another threat nearby.

9
00:00:28,553 --> 00:00:32,025
Think this is the work
of the Kingdom of Yelenetta?

10
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:33,140
Most likely.

11
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:34,899
Yelenetta's attacking this village?

12
00:00:35,248 --> 00:00:41,551
Baron, there's a good chance this wyvern
has a small group of elite knights in tow.

13
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:42,640
Be careful.

14
00:00:42,728 --> 00:00:43,889
Right.

15
00:00:45,899 --> 00:00:49,960
Although at that altitude,
ballista bolts won't reach it.

16
00:00:50,462 --> 00:00:53,397
That leaves one option.
We'll deploy the prototype.

17
00:01:05,802 --> 00:01:10,915
EASYGOING TERRITORY DEFENSE
BY THE OPTIMISTIC LORD

18
00:01:10,916 --> 00:01:13,597
EPISODE 10: A SECRET WEAPON'S
VILLAINOUS ATTACK ON THE HOMELAND

19
00:02:27,528 --> 00:02:31,342
We'll soon be in enemy territory,
Your Highness.

20
00:02:31,677 --> 00:02:36,623
The wyvern is already scouting
Seatoh from above.

21
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:42,281
I can't believe they made me lead
the invasion of such a remote village.

22
00:02:43,035 --> 00:02:48,987
I'm Prince Unimog Yelenetta, eighth son
of Yelenetta Kingdom, for pity's sake.

23
00:02:49,531 --> 00:02:55,860
The king commanded you to lead
this operation due to its importance.

24
00:02:56,489 --> 00:03:02,930
Yelenetta Kingdom has long been rivals
with the neighboring Kingdom of Scuderia.

25
00:03:04,609 --> 00:03:07,769
However, it is now time to settle things
with Scuderia once and for all.

26
00:03:07,856 --> 00:03:13,420
You have been entrusted to lead
our glorious vanguard, Prince Unimog.

27
00:03:14,657 --> 00:03:19,911
Conquering a remote village like this
will be a walk in the park.

28
00:03:21,148 --> 00:03:23,046
We should be there soon.

29
00:03:25,917 --> 00:03:28,213
- Whoa!
- What is that?

30
00:03:28,302 --> 00:03:30,377
Wh-Why is there a fortress city here?

31
00:03:30,907 --> 00:03:34,086
How did they build something like this
in this remote region?

32
00:03:34,219 --> 00:03:35,219
You imbecile!

33
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:39,485
There's no way they could've constructed
a fortress city so easily!

34
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:44,048
They've merely built a facade
that makes it look like a fortress city.

35
00:03:44,259 --> 00:03:47,299
We will advance and take their land.

36
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,904
- H-Hold on.
- Huh?

37
00:03:48,905 --> 00:03:51,185
What if that fortress is the real deal?

38
00:03:51,186 --> 00:03:54,016
You dare to defy me, you insolent oaf?!

39
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,973
I'm telling you it's all for show.

40
00:03:56,974 --> 00:03:59,128
F-Forgive me.

41
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:02,464
Now, go destroy those ramparts!

42
00:04:14,081 --> 00:04:15,939
We've barely made a mark on it.

43
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:18,557
I-Impossible. That can't be true.

44
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:20,079
Good afternoon!

45
00:04:20,798 --> 00:04:24,303
I'm Van, the lord of this village.

46
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,079
That child?

47
00:04:26,656 --> 00:04:32,044
What brings you all this way
from the Kingdom of Yelenetta?

48
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:35,139
Y-You imp! How did you know
we're from Yelenetta Kingdom?

49
00:04:35,232 --> 00:04:37,666
So my guess was right.

50
00:04:37,759 --> 00:04:41,597
I was just bluffing that I knew,
but you were quick to admit it.

51
00:04:43,562 --> 00:04:47,493
This village didn't have ramparts
like this before.

52
00:04:47,586 --> 00:04:51,845
How did you turn it into a fortress city?

53
00:04:51,939 --> 00:04:55,560
Oh, the villagers and I worked together
to make the ramparts and facilities.

54
00:04:55,882 --> 00:04:58,194
D-Do you take me for a fool?!

55
00:04:58,286 --> 00:05:00,458
Get down here now!

56
00:05:00,551 --> 00:05:04,156
Don't expect me to go on easy on you
just because you're a child!

57
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:07,853
My wyvern can attack you
from the air, you know!

58
00:05:07,945 --> 00:05:10,534
Your ramparts won't save you!

59
00:05:11,042 --> 00:05:14,000
Send a message to the mage
controlling the wyvern.

60
00:05:14,139 --> 00:05:15,300
Get him to attack them.

61
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:17,699
But there's a chance
he'll be attacked in return—

62
00:05:17,791 --> 00:05:19,819
Imbecile!

63
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:21,846
Wyverns are dragons!

64
00:05:21,939 --> 00:05:22,939
There's no way it'd lose!

65
00:05:23,027 --> 00:05:24,125
R-Right.

66
00:05:24,214 --> 00:05:28,170
Now, it's time you learned
just how terrifying dragons can be.

67
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:32,696
Lady Panamera. If you would.

68
00:05:32,785 --> 00:05:34,015
Huh?

69
00:05:35,729 --> 00:05:36,960
Fire!

70
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,520
Wh-What the...

71
00:05:54,669 --> 00:05:56,137
Those are shuriken.

72
00:05:56,573 --> 00:06:01,492
They're thin and light, so I figured
I'd stuff them inside a bomb of sorts.

73
00:06:03,197 --> 00:06:05,298
This was your "prototype"?

74
00:06:05,299 --> 00:06:09,220
Yes. That's the first time we've used it,
but it seemed moderately successful.

75
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,139
That was a ridiculous amount of force.

76
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:17,769
That could prove to be as much
of a threat as an elemental mage.

77
00:06:18,259 --> 00:06:19,258
Y-You.

78
00:06:19,259 --> 00:06:20,480
You're the king of Scuderia.

79
00:06:21,176 --> 00:06:25,866
Wh-What's the king doing
in such a remote village?

80
00:06:27,026 --> 00:06:30,416
Now then, do you all want to continue?

81
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:40,478
You bunch of cowards!
What are you doing? Protect me!

82
00:06:40,479 --> 00:06:43,358
What's this? You have plenty
of fight left in you, huh?

83
00:06:43,609 --> 00:06:45,361
Lady Panamera?

84
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:51,747
- Whoa.
- The next one won't miss!

85
00:06:55,085 --> 00:06:58,257
The baron is full of surprises.

86
00:06:58,549 --> 00:07:03,306
You said it. Marquis Fertio
has sired one incredible son.

87
00:07:03,682 --> 00:07:08,857
If I remember right, I heard the marquis
drove the baron out of his home.

88
00:07:09,651 --> 00:07:14,699
I doubt he ever imagined someone
with a low-ranking magical aptitude

89
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:17,413
would be capable of such feats.

90
00:07:17,914 --> 00:07:19,457
When we return to the capital,

91
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:22,672
we'll have to reconsider
our research into magical aptitudes.

92
00:07:28,139 --> 00:07:32,563
Now then, Your Highness.
Might you tell us what your strategy was?

93
00:07:33,898 --> 00:07:36,319
There's no way I'm telling you.

94
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:38,863
Well, that is unfortunate.

95
00:07:38,864 --> 00:07:40,826
Viscountess Cayenne?

96
00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:46,569
Should I rip out your fingernails
one at a time or gouge out your eyes?

97
00:07:48,129 --> 00:07:49,129
Which would you prefer?

98
00:07:50,946 --> 00:07:54,322
Please don't! Okay! I'll talk! I'll talk!

99
00:07:56,400 --> 00:08:02,979
Yelenetta Kingdom has been planning
this invasion for several years now.

100
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,458
Oh?

101
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:10,330
We start by conquering this village
in Marquis Fertio's lands.

102
00:08:10,988 --> 00:08:14,889
We assumed taking control of
this remote village would be easy.

103
00:08:16,902 --> 00:08:20,597
Yet you were bested here.
How embarrassing.

104
00:08:20,598 --> 00:08:23,160
Were you planning to invade
other territories as well?

105
00:08:23,635 --> 00:08:28,472
At this very moment, a separate force
is attacking the city we're truly after.

106
00:08:28,904 --> 00:08:31,151
Which one would that be?

107
00:08:32,187 --> 00:08:35,340
The fortress city of Scudet.

108
00:08:39,659 --> 00:08:42,855
My threats got the information out of him.

109
00:08:43,158 --> 00:08:46,527
I see. So Scudet is their target?

110
00:08:46,613 --> 00:08:50,630
I believe Your Majesty and I should
hasten back to the royal capital.

111
00:08:51,018 --> 00:08:56,115
We should marshal our knights at once
and ride to the defense of Scudet.

112
00:08:56,849 --> 00:09:01,990
I'm broadly in agreement.
But allow me to add one request.

113
00:09:02,379 --> 00:09:03,379
What is it?

114
00:09:03,899 --> 00:09:06,153
Baron Van Nei Fertio.

115
00:09:06,154 --> 00:09:10,101
I request you join us
in our defense of Scudet.

116
00:09:10,924 --> 00:09:11,965
Huh?

117
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:14,177
You're against the idea, boy?

118
00:09:18,210 --> 00:09:21,409
Normally, I wouldn't be able to say no
in this situation, but I won't yield.

119
00:09:22,009 --> 00:09:24,830
Because I want to hole up in this village.

120
00:09:25,557 --> 00:09:28,127
I am greatly honored by your request,

121
00:09:28,213 --> 00:09:33,437
but leaving this village while it's still
developing is akin to abandoning it.

122
00:09:33,438 --> 00:09:37,420
Even though it possesses weapons
capable of firing holes in wyverns

123
00:09:37,421 --> 00:09:42,003
and defenses that can fell
armored lizards and dragons,

124
00:09:42,089 --> 00:09:44,145
you claim it is still "developing"?

125
00:09:44,616 --> 00:09:49,369
Yes. I've barely completed
a tenth of what I envision.

126
00:09:49,455 --> 00:09:53,352
There's much more
I'd like to make for it.

127
00:09:57,292 --> 00:09:59,648
You really are amusing, boy.

128
00:09:59,990 --> 00:10:04,145
I can't wait to see what you make that's
even more incredible than all of that.

129
00:10:04,459 --> 00:10:05,401
However...

130
00:10:05,402 --> 00:10:07,319
You should accept this request.

131
00:10:07,614 --> 00:10:11,837
Every noble must come to
the nation's aid when it's in danger.

132
00:10:12,344 --> 00:10:16,820
That's essentially the covenant you forge
when you become a noble.

133
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:20,451
Very well.

134
00:10:20,452 --> 00:10:24,041
If it's a noble's duty, I'll participate.

135
00:10:24,042 --> 00:10:27,208
However, I still have
my responsibilities as a lord.

136
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:30,799
Please allow me to organize
my troops myself.

137
00:10:32,192 --> 00:10:33,923
You may do as you wish.

138
00:10:36,204 --> 00:10:39,539
I finally got the village's
defenses all set up,

139
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:43,256
and now I'm being told to leave
the village and go fight.

140
00:10:43,889 --> 00:10:48,788
At any rate, can I ask you to protect
this village as its acting lord, Esparda?

141
00:10:48,789 --> 00:10:53,645
Of course, but will you
be all right without me?

142
00:10:54,025 --> 00:10:56,558
Well, I am a bit anxious about that,

143
00:10:56,685 --> 00:11:00,739
but only someone with your ability
can serve as lord in my stead.

144
00:11:01,289 --> 00:11:02,370
I understand.

145
00:11:03,339 --> 00:11:07,440
Dee, you and the Seatoh Chivalric Order
will come with me, right?

146
00:11:07,529 --> 00:11:09,089
Yes, sir.

147
00:11:09,213 --> 00:11:11,073
Till and Khamsin, it'll be dangerous, so—

148
00:11:11,074 --> 00:11:13,638
I'm coming, too!
I'm coming with you, okay?

149
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:14,797
I'm coming, too.

150
00:11:15,335 --> 00:11:18,147
Oh, right. Understood.

151
00:11:19,099 --> 00:11:22,159
But will this be enough?

152
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:26,337
People in the royal capital won't claim I
showed up with too few troops, will they?

153
00:11:27,786 --> 00:11:32,996
This will be more than enough
to those who know your might,

154
00:11:32,997 --> 00:11:35,230
but to those who don't? Hard to say.

155
00:11:35,231 --> 00:11:36,472
Excuse me.

156
00:11:37,092 --> 00:11:39,946
Do you mind if we accept
a quest to guard you?

157
00:11:39,947 --> 00:11:41,393
Huh? You'd do that?

158
00:11:41,394 --> 00:11:44,661
Normally, we'd have nothing
to do with any wars.

159
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:47,681
But we don't mind accepting
a quest to guard you.

160
00:11:48,219 --> 00:11:50,245
Ah, I'm glad to hear it!

161
00:11:50,246 --> 00:11:53,528
Then, could you reach out
to the other adventurers, too?

162
00:11:53,529 --> 00:11:57,087
Tell them I'll pay one large gold
and five gold per person.

163
00:11:57,173 --> 00:11:59,671
You'll give us that much?

164
00:11:59,672 --> 00:12:01,790
You're risking your lives, after all.

165
00:12:01,876 --> 00:12:06,620
Thank you for this.
I'm sure everyone will gladly accept.

166
00:12:06,706 --> 00:12:09,077
You're coming with us, right, Kusala?

167
00:12:09,078 --> 00:12:11,323
You're forcing me to do stuff again?

168
00:12:11,663 --> 00:12:17,043
To be honest, it's because I don't
have a suitable scout among my knights.

169
00:12:17,129 --> 00:12:20,008
Well, that's true.

170
00:12:20,009 --> 00:12:25,604
But if it's a quest, I'd at least like
to be asked whether I'll accept it or not.

171
00:12:25,605 --> 00:12:31,240
Huh? But if you don't accept the quest,
you can't come to the barbecue.

172
00:12:31,241 --> 00:12:33,669
What?! I'd miss out on the barbecue?!

173
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:36,591
Then, sure, I'm coming! Of course I am!

174
00:12:37,949 --> 00:12:38,949
Boy.

175
00:12:41,047 --> 00:12:44,856
I'm returning to Count Ferdinatto
to report all of this,

176
00:12:44,857 --> 00:12:48,282
but after, I'll round up my troops
and head for Scudet at once.

177
00:12:48,539 --> 00:12:50,039
Then, we might see each other there.

178
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:51,995
What weapons are you taking?

179
00:12:53,908 --> 00:12:56,735
I'd like to take some
of my creations with me,

180
00:12:56,822 --> 00:12:59,866
but I can't bring any ballistae
as they are right now.

181
00:12:59,952 --> 00:13:01,170
In that case...

182
00:13:01,865 --> 00:13:04,301
I'll bring my marionette.

183
00:13:04,387 --> 00:13:05,518
Your marionette?

184
00:13:05,953 --> 00:13:07,344
Wait, you mean...

185
00:13:11,649 --> 00:13:14,809
This will be the Seatoh
Chivalric Order's first campaign.

186
00:13:15,490 --> 00:13:18,870
Our mission is to defend our largest
neighbor, the fortress city of Scudet.

187
00:13:20,409 --> 00:13:21,909
Our foes are knights from
the Kingdom of Yelenetta.

188
00:13:22,006 --> 00:13:25,323
They've tested our nation's borders
countless times,

189
00:13:25,422 --> 00:13:28,251
and unlike us,
they'll be very experienced.

190
00:13:28,789 --> 00:13:30,470
However, there's nothing to fear.

191
00:13:31,189 --> 00:13:32,909
We won't be going to the front lines.

192
00:13:34,689 --> 00:13:35,929
What does he mean?

193
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,758
So how do we defeat the enemy?

194
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:42,990
Because our goal is for everyone here
to return to this village, safe and sound.

195
00:13:43,575 --> 00:13:48,454
As your lord, I'm responsible for
the lives you're entrusting me with.

196
00:13:49,089 --> 00:13:51,429
I'll do everything in my power
to protect all of you.

197
00:13:51,811 --> 00:13:54,941
So cherish your own lives as well.

198
00:13:55,590 --> 00:14:01,629
Then, once we're done with this battle,
let's develop this village together...

199
00:14:02,958 --> 00:14:05,360
and enjoy another barbecue!

200
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:08,230
Scudet's been attacked?

201
00:14:08,319 --> 00:14:12,804
Yes. The Kingdom of Yelenetta
has dispatched soldiers.

202
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:19,332
But Scudet's impregnable.
It won't fall that easily.

203
00:14:19,953 --> 00:14:22,574
We'll marshal the troops
and ride out immediately.

204
00:14:22,929 --> 00:14:23,928
Yes, sir.

205
00:14:23,929 --> 00:14:27,931
Send emissaries to the neighboring lords
to request troops from them as well.

206
00:14:28,473 --> 00:14:34,226
The village governed by your son,
Lord Van, is near Scudet, so should we—

207
00:14:34,227 --> 00:14:37,644
That village won't have
any troops to dispatch.

208
00:14:37,645 --> 00:14:41,646
They can barely earn enough to eat.

209
00:14:41,647 --> 00:14:45,691
Still, according to the merchants
who came to the royal capital,

210
00:14:45,692 --> 00:14:48,317
Lord Van has earned the title
of baron for defeating a dragon.

211
00:14:48,318 --> 00:14:49,485
Drivel.

212
00:14:49,486 --> 00:14:54,614
Van doesn't possess elemental magic.
There's no way he could defeat a dragon.

213
00:14:54,905 --> 00:14:59,574
That may be true,
but Lord Van isn't a normal child.

214
00:14:59,575 --> 00:15:02,201
He might have done
something extraordinary—

215
00:15:02,202 --> 00:15:04,245
Just hurry up with the preparations.

216
00:15:04,829 --> 00:15:06,309
We're heading to Scudet at once.

217
00:15:07,129 --> 00:15:08,129
Yes, sir.

218
00:15:09,415 --> 00:15:12,363
FORTRESS CITY OF SCUDET, SOUTH GATE

219
00:15:12,695 --> 00:15:16,224
Impossible. Scudet's impregnable
ramparts have been...

220
00:15:17,926 --> 00:15:22,410
Damn that Yelenetta,
employing so many wyvern squads...

221
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,759
We're withdrawing to regroup!

222
00:15:25,439 --> 00:15:26,439
Yes, sir!

223
00:15:26,749 --> 00:15:29,080
Scuderia's reinforcements are here!

224
00:15:29,081 --> 00:15:30,159
Take this!

225
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:33,820
What's that weapon?

226
00:15:36,715 --> 00:15:39,700
Lord Jalpa! Our forces
have nearly been wiped out!

227
00:15:39,834 --> 00:15:41,304
Wh-What?

228
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:47,250
Is this the end?

229
00:15:49,410 --> 00:15:51,954
They're leaving without finishing us off?

230
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:53,470
What in the world is going on?

231
00:15:55,710 --> 00:15:57,910
FORTRESS CITY SCUDET'S WEST GATE

232
00:16:10,215 --> 00:16:12,371
Wh-What is that thing?

233
00:16:13,090 --> 00:16:16,091
Hurry up and summon
all of our wyverns here!

234
00:16:16,092 --> 00:16:17,909
Yes, sir! At once!

235
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:20,236
Automaton: Uno!

236
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,099
Damn it.

237
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:27,370
Hurry up and crush that thing!

238
00:16:30,962 --> 00:16:34,306
Arte, you're incredible!
I can't believe you can do that!

239
00:16:34,801 --> 00:16:38,804
Who would've believed Scudet
could get conquered so easily?

240
00:16:38,805 --> 00:16:42,685
They must have used those wyverns
and that new weapon.

241
00:16:42,686 --> 00:16:45,189
It seems the damage on
the south gate side is huge.

242
00:16:45,703 --> 00:16:49,222
Scuderia's knights should be
responding over there.

243
00:16:49,223 --> 00:16:54,244
Although they'll probably be forced
to retreat with Scudet in this state.

244
00:16:56,046 --> 00:16:57,634
I don't want to overdo it,

245
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:01,711
but if we draw the enemies to us,
that'll provide some support, right?

246
00:17:02,269 --> 00:17:05,309
All right. Let's keep this up
and buy the knights some time to retreat.

247
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,656
- Yes, sir.
- There they are! Over here!

248
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:14,800
I'll protect you, Lady Arte!

249
00:17:14,892 --> 00:17:16,085
I'm firing!

250
00:17:19,249 --> 00:17:20,329
We're going to fight, too!

251
00:17:21,289 --> 00:17:22,289
Yeah!

252
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,065
Aim for that group!

253
00:17:24,657 --> 00:17:27,365
Whoopsie. Can't let you go doing that.

254
00:17:28,549 --> 00:17:30,750
Sorry, but we can't afford to lose.

255
00:17:31,506 --> 00:17:33,244
I feel bad for you.

256
00:17:36,362 --> 00:17:38,501
Good work, everyone.

257
00:17:45,539 --> 00:17:46,539
Thank you, Arte.

258
00:17:46,959 --> 00:17:47,959
Damn it.

259
00:17:48,085 --> 00:17:50,743
Crush them with all of our forces!

260
00:17:53,991 --> 00:17:56,268
Ah, we lured a lot to us.

261
00:17:56,269 --> 00:17:59,855
Well, I think we've bought them
enough time to escape.

262
00:18:00,109 --> 00:18:01,849
Everyone, it's time to pull back.

263
00:18:02,195 --> 00:18:06,441
Are we really running away?
We might actually win this, you know.

264
00:18:06,571 --> 00:18:08,736
Remember what I said at the start?

265
00:18:08,823 --> 00:18:13,459
Our number one goal is for everyone
to make it home in one piece.

266
00:18:14,369 --> 00:18:18,450
If anyone dies, I won't be happy
at all, even if we do win.

267
00:18:19,690 --> 00:18:21,170
Or does anyone here have a death wish?

268
00:18:24,162 --> 00:18:27,370
Then, let's all run away
as fast as we can.

269
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:28,585
Yes, sir!

270
00:18:31,751 --> 00:18:35,654
Lord Jalpa, what's our next move?

271
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:39,427
We must retake Scudet.

272
00:18:39,729 --> 00:18:43,372
We'll reorganize our knights.
Make the arrangements at once.

273
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:44,460
Yes, sir.

274
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:47,068
Still...

275
00:18:47,851 --> 00:18:50,676
I'm surprised we made it back alive.

276
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:53,279
What in the world happened?

277
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,280
Father.

278
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:58,280
Murcia? You're late. Where were you?

279
00:18:58,873 --> 00:19:00,570
My apologies.

280
00:19:02,011 --> 00:19:04,725
Marquis Jalpa Bul Ati Fertio.

281
00:19:05,234 --> 00:19:08,330
You're making the youngster
cower, you realize.

282
00:19:09,517 --> 00:19:12,400
Your Majesty, I apologize
for that unseemly display.

283
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:14,818
Marquis, you may rise.

284
00:19:14,819 --> 00:19:17,490
What's the situation in Scudet?

285
00:19:18,593 --> 00:19:21,391
Scudet has fallen.

286
00:19:21,392 --> 00:19:23,088
Fallen, you say?!

287
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:29,720
Our knights were attacked by
their new weapon and nearly wiped out.

288
00:19:30,282 --> 00:19:33,655
How did you manage to get away?

289
00:19:33,780 --> 00:19:36,959
Well, for some reason, their wyverns
suddenly stopped pursuing us

290
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,539
and headed for the west gate.

291
00:19:38,540 --> 00:19:42,677
They were most likely drawn there
by Baron Van's reinforcements.

292
00:19:42,678 --> 00:19:45,424
- Huh?
- V-Van?

293
00:19:45,804 --> 00:19:49,646
I suppose we haven't sent word
to your march yet.

294
00:19:49,647 --> 00:19:54,503
Baron Van has developed that
remote village and defeated a dragon,

295
00:19:54,504 --> 00:19:57,714
earning himself a title at a tender age.

296
00:19:58,685 --> 00:20:04,724
But Van isn't an elemental mage.
There's no way he could have—

297
00:20:04,725 --> 00:20:09,327
Marquis, are you suggesting we're lying?

298
00:20:09,328 --> 00:20:11,947
N-No, I would never.

299
00:20:12,539 --> 00:20:15,663
So Van has earned a title?

300
00:20:15,664 --> 00:20:20,478
Young man, are you frustrated your
younger brother earned glory before you?

301
00:20:20,859 --> 00:20:22,340
The opposite.

302
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,040
I'm very proud of him.

303
00:20:29,866 --> 00:20:33,214
Ah, that certainly wore me out.

304
00:20:34,171 --> 00:20:37,606
Lord Van, what are you
planning to do next?

305
00:20:39,258 --> 00:20:41,171
I'm not sure.

306
00:20:41,259 --> 00:20:43,180
I think I've fulfilled my duty as a noble,

307
00:20:43,267 --> 00:20:48,399
but if Scudet isn't retaken, it means
leaving a threat nearby long-term.

308
00:20:49,096 --> 00:20:53,577
Lord Van. This was my first time
actually witnessing war,

309
00:20:53,663 --> 00:20:58,622
but to me, it felt like a terrifying place
where even innocent people are sacrificed.

310
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:02,754
I don't want to go there again
if I can avoid it.

311
00:21:06,191 --> 00:21:10,062
Still, we're allied with Lady Panamera
who's involved in this war,

312
00:21:10,150 --> 00:21:13,630
so I think we'll have to provide
some form of aid.

313
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:18,850
All right.

314
00:21:19,890 --> 00:21:22,369
Let's develop a new weapon.
Next is the catapult.

315
00:21:22,370 --> 00:21:26,886
Deliver some to the battlefield, and we
can claim we provided plenty of support.

316
00:21:35,514 --> 00:21:37,368
It's rather big, isn't it?

317
00:21:37,369 --> 00:21:40,670
How many are you planning to make?

318
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:45,307
I think twenty stationary ones
and five mobile ones should suffice.

319
00:21:45,656 --> 00:21:51,343
Oh, but I guess it'd be difficult
to transport that many to Scudet.

320
00:21:51,824 --> 00:21:54,842
The roads there were
in pretty bad condition.

321
00:21:57,774 --> 00:22:01,054
Oh, right. I can just make them on-site.

322
00:22:01,491 --> 00:22:04,335
That's right. That's an option, too.

323
00:22:05,079 --> 00:22:08,059
Now, let's start our strategy meeting
in preparation for tomorrow!

324
00:22:17,226 --> 00:22:20,688
TRANSLATION: JOHN PICKETT

325
00:22:20,689 --> 00:22:24,283
TIMING: ANDY ELLIS
EDITING: SMR

326
00:22:24,284 --> 00:22:27,713
QUALITY CONTROL: RILEY DALTON
